**Round 05, Section 1 done — the phased plan with decision gates.**

I translated the Strategy Document's designated convert-to path (Option 1, Restructure-first) into a four-phase capital-staging architecture separated by three binding, evidence-completion decision gates:

- **P0 Offer & acceptance** → **P1 Validation-and-IP tranche** → **P2 First-reference tranche** → **P3 Growth-capital release**
- Inter-phase gates: **T1 (acceptance) + T2 (capped down-world)** open P1; **Gate A (IP/FTO) + Gate B (validation)** open P2; **Gate C (first reference)** opens P3.
- Core design principle: gates are **event-driven, not date-driven**, every release is abandonable with cost/time ceilings (T5/T6/T7), and **no growth capital exists in the plan until all three gates clear**. The §7 override (T8) bars any release with an open unmitigated High gate.
- The **Anchor escalation (T3)** is held as a P2 reconfiguration, contingent on a field-of-use ring-fence — no extra phase.
- **Mandatory DISSENT flag** logged: the phasing must *not* inherit the deck's Month 10/16/25 calendar, because W3/W9 show those dates are campaign-start, not validated numbers, and qualification runs ~2–3 yr/site. That makes T2 ("parallel and readable within ~12 months for a bounded spend") the binding uncertainty of the whole plan — and the structure halts cleanly at P0/P1 if it fails.

