**Part A — 9 sealed, blind failure modes** (core 8 + PILOT; CHOKEPOINT phase-scoped out, its geo limbs carried by SPOT/WATERSHED). Each written 24-months-out, anchored to its own seat's evidence, none referencing another:
- **CRUCIBLE** — bench passes, scale never does (the soft/ambiguous read laundered through Gate B)
- **SPOT** — royalty base real but the price world wasn't; banded model overridden under deal pressure
- **CLAIM** — nothing exclusive to license (option lapses) + thin moat designed around once the number is public
- **ROYALTY** — the signable narrow base is too thin to clear returns; "real but value-destroying close"
- **MILL** — buyer evaluates, then builds it itself; anchor without a replication ring-fence is a self-substitution accelerant
- **CAPITAL** — pricing discipline and P3 raisability slip; master pair is one mitigation dressed as two
- **WATERSHED** — green claims precede substantiation, technical miss becomes a 10b-5 exposure
- **PILOT** — independent outside-pool line unbuildable inside the ~$0.9M/12-mo envelope, so the gate was never real
- **DISSENT** — the advisor talked itself into the deal it was funding; governance is the amplifier on every other mode

**Part B — Moderator feed-back.** Central finding: governance, not metallurgy, enforces the load-bearing gates. Every mode routed to an earlier/new gate or a named contingency, yielding **5 plan changes** handed to validation + R07: a **G0 neutrality & abandon-spec gate** ahead of T1; **T2 raised to a named outside-pool vendor quote** (not an advisor-authored analysis); a **B2 protocol-lock sub-gate**; **T1 quantitative floors**; and **pulled-forward deliverables**. The four contained-not-removed residuals and the R-REV-8 × R-ADOPT-2 master-pair T2 concentration are ratified unchanged.

